boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: (781) 391-7469 (*this number forwards to the Box Office at The Wilbur when the Chevalier Box Office is not open).
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: The Chevalier Theatre currently does not have a full-time Box Office. The Box Office will be open 2 hours prior and 1 hour after showtime, day of show only. To buy tickets in advance without service fees please visit the Wilbur Theatre Box Office, located at 246 Tremont St, Boston, MA, 02116. Hours are Monday-Saturday 12-6pm.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Cash, Visa, Mastercard, Discover, American Express
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Location: Box Office (the Box Office is located on the right hand side of the theater) Will Call opens two (2) hours prior to the start of the show and closes (1) hour after the start of the show. Will call tickets can be picked up on the night of the show only. Customers must present a photo I.D. matching the name on ticket account. Tickets may NOT be dropped off or left for other guests.

venues.parkingDetail: From Route 93 (North or South): Medford Square is easily accessed from Route 93. Take Exit 32 for Rt. 60 West. At the rotary, follow the parking attendant who will direct you to the suggested parking behind Medford City Hall. From Route 2 (East or West): From Route 2 take Exit 59 and follow the signs for Route 60 East. Stay on Route 60 East through Arlington, and into Medford. Route 60 goes right into Medford Square. When you get to the main intersection in the middle of the square take Riverside Drive to City Hall Mall where you will find the suggested parking behind Medford City Hall. There is also plenty of on street paring (Free after 6pm) and municipal parking lots within a few blocks of the theatre.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible seating policy: The Chevalier Theatre places high priority on the comfort and safety of its patrons. The Chevalier Theatre also recognizes the needs of people with disabilities, as defined by the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) of 1990. Every effort has been made to comply with both ADA and Commonwealth accessibility guidelines to accommodate patrons with disabilities. Accessible seating can be purchased directly via www.ticketmaster.com. Accessible seats will be marked with an ADA icon. For assistance purchasing ADA seats online, please contact Ticketmaster customer service at 800-653-8000. PLEASE NOTE: When a show is over 85% sold any unsold accessible seating will be opened to the general public.

generalInfo.generalRule: Items NOT allowed: NO weapons or firearms, NO cameras, NO recording devices, NO outside food or beverages, NO umbrellas All bags/purses are subject to search upon entry Smoking is NOT permitted. The venue does not permit re-entry. The use of cell phones is strictly prohibited during performances.
generalInfo.childRule: Performances are All Ages unless otherwise noted. Everyone must have a ticket to enter the venue. Parents are encouraged to use reasonable discretion as some concerts/events are not suitable for children.

events.info: Please note all kids 1 and under do not require a ticket they can sit on the lap of a patron
events.pleaseNote: The Event Organizer is requiring all attendees of this event to have received a negative COVID-19 test within 72-hours prior to entering the venue, OR be fully vaccinated against COVID-19. In attending the event, you certify and attest that you and all individuals in your party attending the event will abide by the following regulations: All fans will provide printed proof of a negative COVID-19 test within 72-hours prior to entering the venue, OR be fully vaccinated against COVID-19 (at least two weeks after final dose) and provide printed proof of immunization. Unvaccinated fans under 12 years of age will be required to take a COVID-19 diagnostic test within 72-hours before the event and will provide proof of negative result prior to entering the venue. Entry requirements and venue protocols are subject to change. Be sure to check the event venue website closer to your event date for the latest information.

venues.name: Toyota Oakdale Theatre

boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: Box Office and event info - 203-265-1501 Administrative offices - 203-269-8721 Group discounts are available for many of our shows. Minimum requirements, discounts and payment policies vary from event to event. Please contact Group Sales for event specific information at 203-269-8721
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Due to the ongoing global pandemic, and to protect the health and safety of our guests and venue staff members, the box office at Oakdale Theatre will be open on-day-of-show only. If you’d like to purchase tickets, please visit us at www.livenation.com. If you’re looking to obtain a refund for a show that was either canceled, postponed or rescheduled, please visit us at www.livenation.com/refund for more information. We look forward to seeing you at our next show at Oakdale Theatre
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Cash, MasterCard, Visa, American Express and Discover cards. Credit cards will only be accepted from the account holder and picture ID is required. NO CHECKS OR SECOND PARTY CREDIT CARDS ARE ACCEPTED.Concessions stands accept cash only..
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Will Call is open during regular business hours and on event nights. Any unclaimed Will Call will be brought to the Administrative Offices for latecomers. Picture ID is required for all Will Call. The box office will not accept tickets to be left at Will Call. Please plan accordingly.

venues.parkingDetail: All parking is on site. General parking is included in the price of your ticket. Premier parking is located in the lot closest to the main entrance of the facility for an additional charge and may be purchased in advance at all points of sale. Premier parking may also be purchased just prior to show time at the entrance to the lot. Sales are cash only and are subject to availability. Parking for the disabled is located in the spaces directly in front of the theater for no additional charge and is available to patrons who possess a handicapped parking sticker, hang tag or license plate.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Theater and all facilities are fully ADA accessible. Elevator access to all levels of the facility. Special seating is available for patrons with mobility impairments, visual impairments and hearing impairments. Infra-red hearing devices are available for all shows free of charge (ID required) at the Administrative offices.

generalInfo.generalRule: There is no dress code however shirts and shoes are required. This is a non-smoking facility. A smoking area is located outside of the lobby for attendees. Camera Policy: Personal cameras are allowed in the venue. Flash photography, video and removable lens cameras are not permitted without venue approval. No laser pointers, weapons, large bags. No outside food or beverages are permitted into the facility. Concessions : The theater offers a variety of concessions items. Traditional fare is available at our concessions stands. A full bar is offered as well as beer and wine for adults 21 years and older. Picture ID is required for the purchase of alcoholic beverages. Concessions items are cash only.
generalInfo.childRule: Oakdale Theatre offers a wide variety of programming. Parents and guardians are urged to contact the box office for information on a specific show. For most events, children who have reached their second birthday must have a ticket and occupy their own seat. The availability of discounts for children is also event specific. Please ask at the time of purchase since we are not able to refund all or part of your purchase price. Please visit Oakdale Theatre at www.livenation.com for more information on a specific event.

events.info: The Event Organizer is requiring all attendees of this event to have received a qualifying negative COVID-19 test OR be fully vaccinated against COVID-19. In attending the event, you certify and attest that you and all individuals in your party attending the event will abide by the following regulations: All fans 12 years of age or older will provide printed or digital proof of a qualifying negative COVID-19 test OR must be fully vaccinated against COVID-19 (at least 14 days after final dose) and provide printed or digital proof of vaccination. Children under 12 years of age will not be required to provide proof of a qualifying negative COVID-19 test. Per the City of Boston health public health order, face masks are required for all guests over the age of 2, unless actively eating or drinking as permitted, while in the venue. Entry requirements are subject to change, please visit www.TDGarden.com/playitsafe for more information and FAQ's.
events.pleaseNote: Originally scheduled for September 13th, 2021. Previously purchased tickets will be honored for the new date. Ticket Transfer Is Temporarily Unavailable. My Chemical Romance wants fans to have the best access to tickets. To ensure that all orders adhere to the published ticket limits, we'll perform a final review after the general sale. During this time, ticket transfers will be unavailable. Please note, delivery may be delayed up until 72 hours from the show date. Check back soon to send tickets to friends and family. Guests attending TD Garden events are advised that laptops, bags, backpacks, luggage, coolers, parcels, briefcases and like articles will be strictly prohibited from the facility. All guests may be subject to search of their person and/or possessions. Patrons with prohibited articles will be turned away and no storage or "check-in area" will be provided. Enforcement will be without exceptions.

ada.adaCustomCopy:
Accessible seating is reserved for the exclusive use of disabled patrons and their guests. The purchase or use of these seating locations by non-disabled individuals is strictly prohibited and may result in ejection and/or forfeiture of ticket price.  If the disabled individual cannot attend an event for which he/she has purchased tickets, call the DCU Center Box Office prior to the event taking place for further instructions.

DCU Center tickets for patrons with accessible needs, subject to availability, may be purchased in the following ways:

1) Order online at Ticketmaster.com

2) Call the DCU Center Box Office (508) 929-0164

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Due to the ongoing global pandemic, and to protect the health and safety of our guests and venue staff members, the box office at Xfinity Theatre will be open on-day-of-show only. If you’d like to purchase tickets, please visit us at www.livenation.com. If you’re looking to obtain a refund for a show that was either canceled, postponed or rescheduled, please visit us at www.livenation.com/refund for more information. We look forward to seeing you at our next show at Xfinity Theatre
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Cash, MasterCard, Visa, American Express and Discover cards
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Will Call is distributed from designated windows at the Box Office which is at the main entrance to the facility. Patrons will be asked to present their picture ID and the credit card used to make the purchase. Patrons are not permitted to leave tickets at Will Call for another party - please plan accordingly.

venues.parkingDetail: Premier Parking is available for purchase in advance or on the day of the show (subject to availability) for most events. The Premier Parking lot is located at the main entrance to the venue at 61 Savitt Way. A Premier Parking hang tag is required for entry to the Premier Parking lot. Hang tags are available for purchase in advance or on the day of the show (subject to availability) for most events. Oversized vehicle parking is extremely limited and is sold first come first served and normally sells out on each event. Purchase in advance by adding Premier Parking to your ticket purchase when buying on LiveNation.com. Hang tags will be mailed by the venue no later than 10 days prior to the event. Premier Parking may also be purchased in advance at the Toyota Presents Oakdale Theatre Box Office in Wallingford, CT. Day of show purchases can be made at the entrance to the Premier lot - subject to availability. Rates vary according to the event and type of vehicle. Cash or credit card is accepted. ADA Accessible parking is located within the Premier Parking lot adjacent to the main gates. In an effort to provide ADA Accessible parking to our guests who need it, we require guests to display a valid ADA Accessible hangtag or license plate. ADA parking is available on a first come first served basis.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Seating for the disabled is available throughout the facility including lawn area. All wheelchair locations can be accessed via ramps. Adjacent companion seating is available subject to availability.

generalInfo.generalRule: ALL EVENTS ARE RAIN OR SHINE. There are no cancellations or refunds due to inclement weather. Re-entry to the facility is not permitted. The XFINITY Theatre is a non-smoking facility. Smoking is prohibited in the pavilion and all covered areas. All patrons are subject to search prior to entering the facility gates including the use of metal detectors. Patrons are permitted to bring outside food into the venue. Food must be in a gallon size plastic bag. Patrons are allowed to bring in one factory sealed bottle of water, up to one liter in volume (subject to artist approval). The following items are NOT permitted - Alcohol, drugs, fireworks, weapons of any type, signs or banners, coolers, glass containers, laser pointers, selfie sticks, animals (with the exception of service dogs), or backpacks. Camera Policy: Personal cameras are allowed in the venue. Flash photography, video and removable lens cameras are not permitted without venue approval. Selfie sticks are not permitted in the venue. The following items MAY BE prohibited depending on the event, expected attendance or artist request: Small lawn chairs not exceeding 9" in height, blankets and umbrellas. When umbrellas are permitted they cannot be pointed. Specially designed lawn chairs are available for rent for a nominal fee.
generalInfo.childRule: Unless otherwise specified, all patrons 2 years of age and older require a ticket. Management is not responsible for artistic content and therefore we ask that parents use their discretion when deciding whether to purchase tickets for children.

generalInfo.generalRule: Rules and Restrictions: All events take place rain or shine. No refunds or exchanges. No lawn chairs. No food or beverages (except factory-sealed bottles of water). There is NO SMOKING allowed anywhere at the venue. No Re-Admission Ticket limit of 8 per purchase is standard (with some exceptions). Backpacks and Large Bags: Rockland Trust Bank Pavilion strongly discourages customers from bringing backpacks and large bags (over 1 gallon size) to the Pavilion. All backpacks and large bags will be subject to a thorough inspection at a designated entry gate and may delay your entry into the Pavilion. Camera Policy: Personal, non-professional cameras are allowed in the venue unless they are prohibited by the artist. Flash photography, video and removable lens cameras are not permitted without venue approval. Group Sales: No group discounts. Functions may be booked through the venue administration office. Weapons Prohibited: Guests, including law enforcement personnel not present in an official capacity, are prohibited from bringing weapons into the venue. Rockland Trust Bank Pavilion does not provide weapon lockers. Weapons may not be checked in at the Guest Services kiosk. Weapons include, but are not limited to, the following: firearms, explosives, stun guns, handcuffs, brass knuckles, sticks, clubs, batons, martial arts instruments, pepper spray, tear gas, and knives with blades over 2 inches in length. Guests found in possession of the above-mentioned items will be asked to remove the item from the venue or dispose of it. Guests who refuse to comply will be evicted from the venue.

generalInfo.generalRule: What is Allowed in the Gates? The following is a list of items and whether they are typically allowed into the venue or not. Sometimes a specific tour may require a different policy on certain items. All items that are allowed in are subject to a thorough search from our security team. »Bags or Purses? No, except for a small clutch purse or a clear tote with a maximum size of 12" Wide x 12" High x 6" Deep. »Lawn Chairs? Chair rentals are available for $5! Pick them up when you arrive and then leave them where they are when you leave. Fast, simple and hassle-free! (If you wish to bring your own lawn chair, please be aware that they MUST adhere to the size limitation policy and you will have a thorough search at a specific location that will make entry in the venue slower.) »Blankets? If you have a lawn seating ticket, yes. »Food & Drink? No, except for one factory-sealed bottle of water, 20 oz. or less, per person »Refillable Water Bottles? Yes, but only completely empty. There are fill stations inside. »Coolers? No. »Weapons? No. »Cameras? Yes but only non-professional without a detachable lens. »IPads? No. »Video Camera? No. »Selfie Sticks? No. »Drugs? No. »Medications? Yes, but only in the original prescription container with matching ID. »Pets? No. »Poster Tubes? Yes. »Umbrellas? Yes, but may not be open during the performance. We recommend quality rain gear. »Signs? Yes, but please be courteous to others. Lawn Seating The lawn seating is a general admission area behind the reserved pavilion seats. It is not covered and therefore, is exposed to the elements. In the event of inclement weather, we recommend quality rain gear. Umbrellas are allowed but may not be open during the performances. Smoking is prohibited except in one section to the far right of the lawn. If you have trouble walking up inclined surfaces, lawn seating may not be the best option for you. If lawn seating is your only option, please see our staff for assistance. Traffic Please plan ahead and allow for plenty of extra time in the event of heavy traffic so that you do not miss any of the earlier performances. We open the parking lots hours early to accommodate all those that want to arrive early. Drop-Offs & Pick-Ups Please arrive before the rush on both ends of a pick-up and drop-off and do so at the Main Entrance off of Route 11B in Gilford -- 72 Meadowbrook Ln. Tailgating We have several parking areas and we condone and even, promote, responsible tailgating. Tailgating can be a very big part of making the event fun and memorable for you. That being said, the possession or consumption of alcoholic beverages, in our parking areas, actually violates a local Gilford ordinance. Underage drinking and/or intoxication, will most certainly cause you to miss the show and may lead to being arrested. Weather All performances will go on rain or shine. In the event of a weather emergency, like a hurricane, events will most likely be rescheduled. In the event of inclement weather, please use quality rain gear. Umbrellas are allowed but may not be open during performances. Umbrellas Umbrellas are allowed inside the venue and we allow all types of chairs and blankets in the lawn area. We ask that you are courteous and keep your umbrella closed during the performance to not obstruct anyone's view. We recommend wearing ponchos or other rain gear. The show will go on rain or shine. Weapons There are absolutely no weapons of any kind permitted into the venue including small pocket knives. There will be bag searches and pat downs. Any weapons discovered on an individual attempting to enter the venue will be confiscated and we will not be able to return that item to you at any time. Pets There are no pets allowed anywhere on the property. Please contact the box office in advance to coordinate the use of any kind of service animal. No Re-entry Once you enter the pavilion, you will not be permitted to leave the venue and re-enter again so please be sure to bring everything you need with you the first time. Be sure to have your photo ID with you as everyone is carded for alcohol service. Doors The doors or gates to our midway typically open between 90 and 120 minutes prior to the main stage performances starting. We usually have a lot going on include excellent regional acts playing on the Magic Hat Stage so please come in early, enjoy everything we have to offer and assure your party not missing any of the show all at the same time. Resale Tickets When the artist approves to do so, we offer our customers the ability to buy and sell tickets directly from each other for their convenience, comfort and security. For more information on our resell program, go here. Ticket Information There are no refunds or exchanges on any tickets for any event. GROUP SALES Contact Aubrey at AubreyBrooks@LiveNation.com

boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Once within 10 days of the event, tickets may be placed in "will-call," which means you can pick them up anytime between the time of purchase and the time of the show. You must have a photo ID to show that you are the person that the tickets were purchased for and the credit card used to purchase the tickets must be present.

venues.parkingDetail: We provide ample parking for the events right on the property. A parking pass is required of every vehicle looking to enter the property for the events. There are several different kinds of parking passes including overnight tent site parking passes. Please see the different parking options below. Our parking areas typically open 3 to 4 hours before the show starts. Please review the times on our website as they can change and the time on your tickets and/or passes may no longer be accurate. $65 Ultimate Bath VIP Parking (East) $55 Ultimate Bath VIP Parking (West) $40 Kubota Prime Tailgate Parking $30 MB Tractor Premium Parking $15 Orange Standard Parking $75 Limo/RV Parking $65 Kittery Trading Post Overnight Tent Sites
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: ADA tickets can be purchased online via www.livenation.com. You do not need to call the box office to place an order as all of our accessible tickets are available through www.livenation.com. Look for the logo on the Find Tickets page to view all available accessible seats. We do have accessible seating in every price range, but be advised it does occasionally sell out. We have very limited seating available for guests on the day of the event so please make sure you purchase accessible seating when you order tickets.

generalInfo.generalRule: What is Allowed in the Gates? The following is a list of items and whether they are typically allowed into the venue or not. Sometimes a specific tour may require a different policy on certain items. All items that are allowed in are subject to a thorough search from our security team. »Bags or Purses? No, except for a small clutch purse or a clear tote with a maximum size of 12" Wide x 12" High x 6" Deep. »Lawn Chairs? Chair rentals are available for $5! Pick them up when you arrive and then leave them where they are when you leave. Fast, simple and hassle-free! (If you wish to bring your own lawn chair, please be aware that they MUST adhere to the size limitation policy and you will have a thorough search at a specific location that will make entry in the venue slower.) »Blankets? If you have a lawn seating ticket, yes. »Food & Drink? No, except for one factory-sealed bottle of water, 20 oz. or less, per person »Refillable Water Bottles? Yes, but only completely empty. There are fill stations inside. »Coolers? No. »Weapons? No. »Cameras? Yes but only non-professional without a detachable lens. »IPads? No. »Video Camera? No. »Selfie Sticks? No. »Drugs? No. »Medications? Yes, but only in the original prescription container with matching ID. »Pets? No. »Poster Tubes? Yes. »Umbrellas? Yes, but may not be open during the performance. We recommend quality rain gear. »Signs? Yes, but please be courteous to others. Lawn Seating The lawn seating is a general admission area behind the reserved pavilion seats. It is not covered and therefore, is exposed to the elements. In the event of inclement weather, we recommend quality rain gear. Umbrellas are allowed but may not be open during the performances. Smoking is prohibited except in one section to the far right of the lawn. If you have trouble walking up inclined surfaces, lawn seating may not be the best option for you. If lawn seating is your only option, please see our staff for assistance. Traffic Please plan ahead and allow for plenty of extra time in the event of heavy traffic so that you do not miss any of the earlier performances. We open the parking lots hours early to accommodate all those that want to arrive early. Drop-Offs & Pick-Ups Please arrive before the rush on both ends of a pick-up and drop-off and do so at the Main Entrance off of Route 11B in Gilford -- 72 Meadowbrook Ln. Tailgating We have several parking areas and we condone and even, promote, responsible tailgating. Tailgating can be a very big part of making the event fun and memorable for you. That being said, the possession or consumption of alcoholic beverages, in our parking areas, actually violates a local Gilford ordinance. Underage drinking and/or intoxication, will most certainly cause you to miss the show and may lead to being arrested. Weather All performances will go on rain or shine. In the event of a weather emergency, like a hurricane, events will most likely be rescheduled. In the event of inclement weather, please use quality rain gear. Umbrellas are allowed but may not be open during performances. Umbrellas Umbrellas are allowed inside the venue and we allow all types of chairs and blankets in the lawn area. We ask that you are courteous and keep your umbrella closed during the performance to not obstruct anyone's view. We recommend wearing ponchos or other rain gear. The show will go on rain or shine. Weapons There are absolutely no weapons of any kind permitted into the venue including small pocket knives. There will be bag searches and pat downs. Any weapons discovered on an individual attempting to enter the venue will be confiscated and we will not be able to return that item to you at any time. Pets There are no pets allowed anywhere on the property. Please contact the box office in advance to coordinate the use of any kind of service animal. No Re-entry Once you enter the pavilion, you will not be permitted to leave the venue and re-enter again so please be sure to bring everything you need with you the first time. Be sure to have your photo ID with you as everyone is carded for alcohol service. Doors The doors or gates to our midway typically open between 90 and 120 minutes prior to the main stage performances starting. We usually have a lot going on include excellent regional acts playing on the Magic Hat Stage so please come in early, enjoy everything we have to offer and assure your party not missing any of the show all at the same time. Resale Tickets When the artist approves to do so, we offer our customers the ability to buy and sell tickets directly from each other for their convenience, comfort and security. For more information on our resell program, go here. Ticket Information There are no refunds or exchanges on any tickets for any event. GROUP SALES Contact Aubrey at AubreyBrooks@LiveNation.com
generalInfo.childRule: Children under 2 are free in general admission areas like lawn seating or on an adult lap in reserved seating areas.

boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: Box Office and event info - 203-265-1501 Administrative offices - 203-269-8721 Group discounts are available for many of our shows. Minimum requirements, discounts and payment policies vary from event to event. Please contact Group Sales for event specific information at 203-269-8721
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Due to the ongoing global pandemic, and to protect the health and safety of our guests and venue staff members, the box office at Oakdale Theatre will be open on-day-of-show only. If you’d like to purchase tickets, please visit us at www.livenation.com. If you’re looking to obtain a refund for a show that was either canceled, postponed or rescheduled, please visit us at www.livenation.com/refund for more information. We look forward to seeing you at our next show at Oakdale Theatre
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Cash, MasterCard, Visa, American Express and Discover cards. Credit cards will only be accepted from the account holder and picture ID is required. NO CHECKS OR SECOND PARTY CREDIT CARDS ARE ACCEPTED.Concessions stands accept cash only..
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Will Call is open during regular business hours and on event nights. Any unclaimed Will Call will be brought to the Administrative Offices for latecomers. Picture ID is required for all Will Call. The box office will not accept tickets to be left at Will Call. Please plan accordingly.

venues.parkingDetail: All parking is on site. General parking is included in the price of your ticket. Premier parking is located in the lot closest to the main entrance of the facility for an additional charge and may be purchased in advance at all points of sale. Premier parking may also be purchased just prior to show time at the entrance to the lot. Sales are cash only and are subject to availability. Parking for the disabled is located in the spaces directly in front of the theater for no additional charge and is available to patrons who possess a handicapped parking sticker, hang tag or license plate.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Theater and all facilities are fully ADA accessible. Elevator access to all levels of the facility. Special seating is available for patrons with mobility impairments, visual impairments and hearing impairments. Infra-red hearing devices are available for all shows free of charge (ID required) at the Administrative offices.

generalInfo.generalRule: There is no dress code however shirts and shoes are required. This is a non-smoking facility. A smoking area is located outside of the lobby for attendees. Camera Policy: Personal cameras are allowed in the venue. Flash photography, video and removable lens cameras are not permitted without venue approval. No laser pointers, weapons, large bags. No outside food or beverages are permitted into the facility. Concessions : The theater offers a variety of concessions items. Traditional fare is available at our concessions stands. A full bar is offered as well as beer and wine for adults 21 years and older. Picture ID is required for the purchase of alcoholic beverages. Concessions items are cash only.
generalInfo.childRule: Oakdale Theatre offers a wide variety of programming. Parents and guardians are urged to contact the box office for information on a specific show. For most events, children who have reached their second birthday must have a ticket and occupy their own seat. The availability of discounts for children is also event specific. Please ask at the time of purchase since we are not able to refund all or part of your purchase price. Please visit Oakdale Theatre at www.livenation.com for more information on a specific event.

events.info: PLEASE NOTE: In the best interest of fans and staff, The Boch Center requires ALL patrons to be fully vaccinated or provide a negative Covid test, taken within the last 72 hours, in order to attend a performance (at-home tests WILL NOT be accepted). Proof of vaccination and matching photo ID will be required prior to entry (photo of vaccination card is acceptable). Masks will be required for all guests per City of Boston requirements. By purchasing tickets to this event, you agree to abide by these, and any other, health and safety measures that may be in effect at the time of the event. Check our venue website for updates to your event as guidelines are subject to change.
events.pleaseNote: This event has been rescheduled from June 10th 2020. Original tickets will be honored for the new date. Ringo Starr & His All Starr Band / The Avett Brothers, originally scheduled for June 10, 2020 has been rescheduled to June 3, 2021. All tickets as originally purchased remain valid for the new date. "This is very difficult for me," said Ringo, "in 30 years I think I've only missed 2 or 3 gigs nevermind a whole tour. But this is how things are for all of us now, I have to stay in just like you have to stay in, and we all know it's the peace and loving thing we do for each other. So we have moved the Spring tour to 2021. My fans know I love them, and I love to play for them and I can't wait to see you all as soon as possible. In the meantime stay safe. Peace and Love to you all."

boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Once within 10 days of the event, tickets may be placed in "will-call," which means you can pick them up anytime between the time of purchase and the time of the show. You must have a photo ID to show that you are the person that the tickets were purchased for and the credit card used to purchase the tickets must be present.

venues.parkingDetail: We provide ample parking for the events right on the property. A parking pass is required of every vehicle looking to enter the property for the events. There are several different kinds of parking passes including overnight tent site parking passes. Please see the different parking options below. Our parking areas typically open 3 to 4 hours before the show starts. Please review the times on our website as they can change and the time on your tickets and/or passes may no longer be accurate. $65 Ultimate Bath VIP Parking (East) $55 Ultimate Bath VIP Parking (West) $40 Kubota Prime Tailgate Parking $30 MB Tractor Premium Parking $15 Orange Standard Parking $75 Limo/RV Parking $65 Kittery Trading Post Overnight Tent Sites
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: ADA tickets can be purchased online via www.livenation.com. You do not need to call the box office to place an order as all of our accessible tickets are available through www.livenation.com. Look for the logo on the Find Tickets page to view all available accessible seats. We do have accessible seating in every price range, but be advised it does occasionally sell out. We have very limited seating available for guests on the day of the event so please make sure you purchase accessible seating when you order tickets.

generalInfo.generalRule: What is Allowed in the Gates? The following is a list of items and whether they are typically allowed into the venue or not. Sometimes a specific tour may require a different policy on certain items. All items that are allowed in are subject to a thorough search from our security team. »Bags or Purses? No, except for a small clutch purse or a clear tote with a maximum size of 12" Wide x 12" High x 6" Deep. »Lawn Chairs? Chair rentals are available for $5! Pick them up when you arrive and then leave them where they are when you leave. Fast, simple and hassle-free! (If you wish to bring your own lawn chair, please be aware that they MUST adhere to the size limitation policy and you will have a thorough search at a specific location that will make entry in the venue slower.) »Blankets? If you have a lawn seating ticket, yes. »Food & Drink? No, except for one factory-sealed bottle of water, 20 oz. or less, per person »Refillable Water Bottles? Yes, but only completely empty. There are fill stations inside. »Coolers? No. »Weapons? No. »Cameras? Yes but only non-professional without a detachable lens. »IPads? No. »Video Camera? No. »Selfie Sticks? No. »Drugs? No. »Medications? Yes, but only in the original prescription container with matching ID. »Pets? No. »Poster Tubes? Yes. »Umbrellas? Yes, but may not be open during the performance. We recommend quality rain gear. »Signs? Yes, but please be courteous to others. Lawn Seating The lawn seating is a general admission area behind the reserved pavilion seats. It is not covered and therefore, is exposed to the elements. In the event of inclement weather, we recommend quality rain gear. Umbrellas are allowed but may not be open during the performances. Smoking is prohibited except in one section to the far right of the lawn. If you have trouble walking up inclined surfaces, lawn seating may not be the best option for you. If lawn seating is your only option, please see our staff for assistance. Traffic Please plan ahead and allow for plenty of extra time in the event of heavy traffic so that you do not miss any of the earlier performances. We open the parking lots hours early to accommodate all those that want to arrive early. Drop-Offs & Pick-Ups Please arrive before the rush on both ends of a pick-up and drop-off and do so at the Main Entrance off of Route 11B in Gilford -- 72 Meadowbrook Ln. Tailgating We have several parking areas and we condone and even, promote, responsible tailgating. Tailgating can be a very big part of making the event fun and memorable for you. That being said, the possession or consumption of alcoholic beverages, in our parking areas, actually violates a local Gilford ordinance. Underage drinking and/or intoxication, will most certainly cause you to miss the show and may lead to being arrested. Weather All performances will go on rain or shine. In the event of a weather emergency, like a hurricane, events will most likely be rescheduled. In the event of inclement weather, please use quality rain gear. Umbrellas are allowed but may not be open during performances. Umbrellas Umbrellas are allowed inside the venue and we allow all types of chairs and blankets in the lawn area. We ask that you are courteous and keep your umbrella closed during the performance to not obstruct anyone's view. We recommend wearing ponchos or other rain gear. The show will go on rain or shine. Weapons There are absolutely no weapons of any kind permitted into the venue including small pocket knives. There will be bag searches and pat downs. Any weapons discovered on an individual attempting to enter the venue will be confiscated and we will not be able to return that item to you at any time. Pets There are no pets allowed anywhere on the property. Please contact the box office in advance to coordinate the use of any kind of service animal. No Re-entry Once you enter the pavilion, you will not be permitted to leave the venue and re-enter again so please be sure to bring everything you need with you the first time. Be sure to have your photo ID with you as everyone is carded for alcohol service. Doors The doors or gates to our midway typically open between 90 and 120 minutes prior to the main stage performances starting. We usually have a lot going on include excellent regional acts playing on the Magic Hat Stage so please come in early, enjoy everything we have to offer and assure your party not missing any of the show all at the same time. Resale Tickets When the artist approves to do so, we offer our customers the ability to buy and sell tickets directly from each other for their convenience, comfort and security. For more information on our resell program, go here. Ticket Information There are no refunds or exchanges on any tickets for any event. GROUP SALES Contact Aubrey at AubreyBrooks@LiveNation.com

venues.parkingDetail: Parking is available for Leader Bank Pavilion patrons at the Seaport Hotel Garage and the EDIC Garage; both are within a short walk of the Pavilion. The Seaport Hotel Garage can be accessed from Seaport Boulevard. The Seaport Boulevard entrance is at the intersection of Seaport Boulevard and B Street, three blocks before the Leader Bank Pavilion. generalInfo.generalRule: Rules and Restrictions: All events take place rain or shine. No refunds or exchanges. No lawn chairs. No food or beverages (except factory-sealed bottles of water). There is NO SMOKING allowed anywhere at the venue. No Re-Admission Ticket limit of 8 per purchase is standard (with some exceptions). Backpacks and Large Bags: Rockland Trust Bank Pavilion strongly discourages customers from bringing backpacks and large bags (over 1 gallon size) to the Pavilion. All backpacks and large bags will be subject to a thorough inspection at a designated entry gate and may delay your entry into the Pavilion. Camera Policy: Personal, non-professional cameras are allowed in the venue unless they are prohibited by the artist. Flash photography, video and removable lens cameras are not permitted without venue approval. Group Sales: No group discounts. Functions may be booked through the venue administration office. Weapons Prohibited: Guests, including law enforcement personnel not present in an official capacity, are prohibited from bringing weapons into the venue. Rockland Trust Bank Pavilion does not provide weapon lockers. Weapons may not be checked in at the Guest Services kiosk. Weapons include, but are not limited to, the following: firearms, explosives, stun guns, handcuffs, brass knuckles, sticks, clubs, batons, martial arts instruments, pepper spray, tear gas, and knives with blades over 2 inches in length. Guests found in possession of the above-mentioned items will be asked to remove the item from the venue or dispose of it. Guests who refuse to comply will be evicted from the venue.
generalInfo.childRule: Children (babies in arms) under 2 years are free if seated in the lap of a ticketed adult. All other children are allowed with a full priced ticket.

generalInfo.generalRule: Rules and Restrictions: All events take place rain or shine. No refunds or exchanges. No lawn chairs. No food or beverages (except factory-sealed bottles of water). There is NO SMOKING allowed anywhere at the venue. No Re-Admission Ticket limit of 8 per purchase is standard (with some exceptions). Backpacks and Large Bags: Rockland Trust Bank Pavilion strongly discourages customers from bringing backpacks and large bags (over 1 gallon size) to the Pavilion. All backpacks and large bags will be subject to a thorough inspection at a designated entry gate and may delay your entry into the Pavilion. Camera Policy: Personal, non-professional cameras are allowed in the venue unless they are prohibited by the artist. Flash photography, video and removable lens cameras are not permitted without venue approval. Group Sales: No group discounts. Functions may be booked through the venue administration office. Weapons Prohibited: Guests, including law enforcement personnel not present in an official capacity, are prohibited from bringing weapons into the venue. Rockland Trust Bank Pavilion does not provide weapon lockers. Weapons may not be checked in at the Guest Services kiosk. Weapons include, but are not limited to, the following: firearms, explosives, stun guns, handcuffs, brass knuckles, sticks, clubs, batons, martial arts instruments, pepper spray, tear gas, and knives with blades over 2 inches in length. Guests found in possession of the above-mentioned items will be asked to remove the item from the venue or dispose of it. Guests who refuse to comply will be evicted from the venue.
generalInfo.childRule: Children (babies in arms) under 2 years are free if seated in the lap of a ticketed adult. All other children are allowed with a full priced ticket.

There are several different kinds of parking passes including overnight tent site parking passes. Please see the different parking options below. Our parking areas typically open 3 to 4 hours before the show starts. Please review the times on our website as they can change and the time on your tickets and/or passes may no longer be accurate. $65 Ultimate Bath VIP Parking (East) $55 Ultimate Bath VIP Parking (West) $40 Kubota Prime Tailgate Parking $30 MB Tractor Premium Parking $15 Orange Standard Parking $75 Limo/RV Parking $65 Kittery Trading Post Overnight Tent Sites

You do not need to call the box office to place an order as all of our accessible tickets are available through www.livenation.com. Look for the logo on the Find Tickets page to view all available accessible seats. We do have accessible seating in every price range, but be advised it does occasionally sell out. We have very limited seating available for guests on the day of the event so please make sure you purchase accessible seating when you order tickets.

generalInfo.generalRule: What is Allowed in the Gates? The following is a list of items and whether they are typically allowed into the venue or not. Sometimes a specific tour may require a different policy on certain items. All items that are allowed in are subject to a thorough search from our security team. »Bags or Purses? No, except for a small clutch purse or a clear tote with a maximum size of 12" Wide x 12" High x 6" Deep. »Lawn Chairs? Chair rentals are available for $5! Pick them up when you arrive and then leave them where they are when you leave. Fast, simple and hassle-free! (If you wish to bring your own lawn chair, please be aware that they MUST adhere to the size limitation policy and you will have a thorough search at a specific location that will make entry in the venue slower.) »Blankets? If you have a lawn seating ticket, yes. »Food & Drink? No, except for one factory-sealed bottle of water, 20 oz. or less, per person »Refillable Water Bottles? Yes, but only completely empty. There are fill stations inside. »Coolers? No. »Weapons? No. »Cameras? Yes but only non-professional without a detachable lens. »IPads? No. »Video Camera? No. »Selfie Sticks? No. »Drugs? No. »Medications? Yes, but only in the original prescription container with matching ID. »Pets? No. »Poster Tubes? Yes. »Umbrellas? Yes, but may not be open during the performance. We recommend quality rain gear. »Signs? Yes, but please be courteous to others. Lawn Seating The lawn seating is a general admission area behind the reserved pavilion seats. It is not covered and therefore, is exposed to the elements. In the event of inclement weather, we recommend quality rain gear. Umbrellas are allowed but may not be open during the performances. Smoking is prohibited except in one section to the far right of the lawn. If you have trouble walking up inclined surfaces, lawn seating may not be the best option for you. If lawn seating is your only option, please see our staff for assistance. Traffic Please plan ahead and allow for plenty of extra time in the event of heavy traffic so that you do not miss any of the earlier performances. We open the parking lots hours early to accommodate all those that want to arrive early. Drop-Offs & Pick-Ups Please arrive before the rush on both ends of a pick-up and drop-off and do so at the Main Entrance off of Route 11B in Gilford -- 72 Meadowbrook Ln. Tailgating We have several parking areas and we condone and even, promote, responsible tailgating. Tailgating can be a very big part of making the event fun and memorable for you. That being said, the possession or consumption of alcoholic beverages, in our parking areas, actually violates a local Gilford ordinance. Underage drinking and/or intoxication, will most certainly cause you to miss the show and may lead to being arrested. Weather All performances will go on rain or shine. In the event of a weather emergency, like a hurricane, events will most likely be rescheduled. In the event of inclement weather, please use quality rain gear. Umbrellas are allowed but may not be open during performances. Umbrellas Umbrellas are allowed inside the venue and we allow all types of chairs and blankets in the lawn area. We ask that you are courteous and keep your umbrella closed during the performance to not obstruct anyone's view. We recommend wearing ponchos or other rain gear. The show will go on rain or shine. Weapons There are absolutely no weapons of any kind permitted into the venue including small pocket knives. There will be bag searches and pat downs. Any weapons discovered on an individual attempting to enter the venue will be confiscated and we will not be able to return that item to you at any time. Pets There are no pets allowed anywhere on the property. Please contact the box office in advance to coordinate the use of any kind of service animal. No Re-entry Once you enter the pavilion, you will not be permitted to leave the venue and re-enter again so please be sure to bring everything you need with you the first time. Be sure to have your photo ID with you as everyone is carded for alcohol service. Doors The doors or gates to our midway typically open between 90 and 120 minutes prior to the main stage performances starting. We usually have a lot going on include excellent regional acts playing on the Magic Hat Stage so please come in early, enjoy everything we have to offer and assure your party not missing any of the show all at the same time. Resale Tickets When the artist approves to do so, we offer our customers the ability to buy and sell tickets directly from each other for their convenience, comfort and security. For more information on our resell program, go here. Ticket Information There are no refunds or exchanges on any tickets for any event. GROUP SALES Contact Aubrey at AubreyBrooks@LiveNation.com
generalInfo.childRule: Children under 2 are free in general admission areas like lawn seating or on an adult lap in reserved seating areas.

venues.parkingDetail: We provide ample parking for the events right on the property. A parking pass is required of every vehicle looking to enter the property for the events. There are several different kinds of parking passes including overnight tent site parking passes. Please see the different parking options below. Our parking areas typically open 3 to 4 hours before the show starts. Please review the times on our website as they can change and the time on your tickets and/or passes may no longer be accurate. $65 Ultimate Bath VIP Parking (East) $55 Ultimate Bath VIP Parking (West) $40 Kubota Prime Tailgate Parking $30 MB Tractor Premium Parking $15 Orange Standard Parking $75 Limo/RV Parking $65 Kittery Trading Post Overnight Tent Sites

You do not need to call the box office to place an order as all of our accessible tickets are available through www.livenation.com. Look for the logo on the Find Tickets page to view all available accessible seats. We do have accessible seating in every price range, but be advised it does occasionally sell out. We have very limited seating available for guests on the day of the event so please make sure you purchase accessible seating when you order tickets.

generalInfo.generalRule: What is Allowed in the Gates? The following is a list of items and whether they are typically allowed into the venue or not. Sometimes a specific tour may require a different policy on certain items. All items that are allowed in are subject to a thorough search from our security team. »Bags or Purses? No, except for a small clutch purse or a clear tote with a maximum size of 12" Wide x 12" High x 6" Deep. »Lawn Chairs? Chair rentals are available for $5! Pick them up when you arrive and then leave them where they are when you leave. Fast, simple and hassle-free! (If you wish to bring your own lawn chair, please be aware that they MUST adhere to the size limitation policy and you will have a thorough search at a specific location that will make entry in the venue slower.) »Blankets? If you have a lawn seating ticket, yes. »Food & Drink? No, except for one factory-sealed bottle of water, 20 oz. or less, per person »Refillable Water Bottles? Yes, but only completely empty. There are fill stations inside. »Coolers? No. »Weapons? No. »Cameras? Yes but only non-professional without a detachable lens. »IPads? No. »Video Camera? No. »Selfie Sticks? No. »Drugs? No. »Medications? Yes, but only in the original prescription container with matching ID. »Pets? No. »Poster Tubes? Yes. »Umbrellas? Yes, but may not be open during the performance. We recommend quality rain gear. »Signs? Yes, but please be courteous to others. Lawn Seating The lawn seating is a general admission area behind the reserved pavilion seats. It is not covered and therefore, is exposed to the elements. In the event of inclement weather, we recommend quality rain gear. Umbrellas are allowed but may not be open during the performances. Smoking is prohibited except in one section to the far right of the lawn. If you have trouble walking up inclined surfaces, lawn seating may not be the best option for you. If lawn seating is your only option, please see our staff for assistance. Traffic Please plan ahead and allow for plenty of extra time in the event of heavy traffic so that you do not miss any of the earlier performances. We open the parking lots hours early to accommodate all those that want to arrive early. Drop-Offs & Pick-Ups Please arrive before the rush on both ends of a pick-up and drop-off and do so at the Main Entrance off of Route 11B in Gilford -- 72 Meadowbrook Ln. Tailgating We have several parking areas and we condone and even, promote, responsible tailgating. Tailgating can be a very big part of making the event fun and memorable for you. That being said, the possession or consumption of alcoholic beverages, in our parking areas, actually violates a local Gilford ordinance. Underage drinking and/or intoxication, will most certainly cause you to miss the show and may lead to being arrested. Weather All performances will go on rain or shine. In the event of a weather emergency, like a hurricane, events will most likely be rescheduled. In the event of inclement weather, please use quality rain gear. Umbrellas are allowed but may not be open during performances. Umbrellas Umbrellas are allowed inside the venue and we allow all types of chairs and blankets in the lawn area. We ask that you are courteous and keep your umbrella closed during the performance to not obstruct anyone's view. We recommend wearing ponchos or other rain gear. The show will go on rain or shine. Weapons There are absolutely no weapons of any kind permitted into the venue including small pocket knives. There will be bag searches and pat downs. Any weapons discovered on an individual attempting to enter the venue will be confiscated and we will not be able to return that item to you at any time. Pets There are no pets allowed anywhere on the property. Please contact the box office in advance to coordinate the use of any kind of service animal. No Re-entry Once you enter the pavilion, you will not be permitted to leave the venue and re-enter again so please be sure to bring everything you need with you the first time. Be sure to have your photo ID with you as everyone is carded for alcohol service. Doors The doors or gates to our midway typically open between 90 and 120 minutes prior to the main stage performances starting. We usually have a lot going on include excellent regional acts playing on the Magic Hat Stage so please come in early, enjoy everything we have to offer and assure your party not missing any of the show all at the same time. Resale Tickets When the artist approves to do so, we offer our customers the ability to buy and sell tickets directly from each other for their convenience, comfort and security. For more information on our resell program, go here. Ticket Information There are no refunds or exchanges on any tickets for any event. GROUP SALES Contact Aubrey at AubreyBrooks@LiveNation.com

There is NO SMOKING allowed anywhere at the venue. No Re-Admission Ticket limit of 8 per purchase is standard (with some exceptions). Backpacks and Large Bags: Rockland Trust Bank Pavilion strongly discourages customers from bringing backpacks and large bags (over 1 gallon size) to the Pavilion. All backpacks and large bags will be subject to a thorough inspection at a designated entry gate and may delay your entry into the Pavilion. Camera Policy: Personal, non-professional cameras are allowed in the venue unless they are prohibited by the artist. Flash photography, video and removable lens cameras are not permitted without venue approval. Group Sales: No group discounts. Functions may be booked through the venue administration office. Weapons Prohibited: Guests, including law enforcement personnel not present in an official capacity, are prohibited from bringing weapons into the venue. Rockland Trust Bank Pavilion does not provide weapon lockers. Weapons may not be checked in at the Guest Services kiosk. Weapons include, but are not limited to, the following: firearms, explosives, stun guns, handcuffs, brass knuckles, sticks, clubs, batons, martial arts instruments, pepper spray, tear gas, and knives with blades over 2 inches in length. Guests found in possession of the above-mentioned items will be asked to remove the item from the venue or dispose of it. Guests who refuse to comply will be evicted from the venue.

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: The Chevalier Theatre currently does not have a full-time Box Office. The Box Office will be open 2 hours prior and 1 hour after showtime, day of show only. To buy tickets in advance without service fees please visit the Wilbur Theatre Box Office, located at 246 Tremont St, Boston, MA, 02116. Hours are Monday-Saturday 12-6pm.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Cash, Visa, Mastercard, Discover, American Express
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Location: Box Office (the Box Office is located on the right hand side of the theater) Will Call opens two (2) hours prior to the start of the show and closes (1) hour after the start of the show. Will call tickets can be picked up on the night of the show only. Customers must present a photo I.D. matching the name on ticket account. Tickets may NOT be dropped off or left for other guests.

venues.parkingDetail: From Route 93 (North or South): Medford Square is easily accessed from Route 93. Take Exit 32 for Rt. 60 West. At the rotary, follow the parking attendant who will direct you to the suggested parking behind Medford City Hall. From Route 2 (East or West): From Route 2 take Exit 59 and follow the signs for Route 60 East. Stay on Route 60 East through Arlington, and into Medford. Route 60 goes right into Medford Square. When you get to the main intersection in the middle of the square take Riverside Drive to City Hall Mall where you will find the suggested parking behind Medford City Hall. There is also plenty of on street paring (Free after 6pm) and municipal parking lots within a few blocks of the theatre.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible seating policy: The Chevalier Theatre places high priority on the comfort and safety of its patrons. The Chevalier Theatre also recognizes the needs of people with disabilities, as defined by the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) of 1990. Every effort has been made to comply with both ADA and Commonwealth accessibility guidelines to accommodate patrons with disabilities. Accessible seating can be purchased directly via www.ticketmaster.com. Accessible seats will be marked with an ADA icon. For assistance purchasing ADA seats online, please contact Ticketmaster customer service at 800-653-8000. PLEASE NOTE: When a show is over 85% sold any unsold accessible seating will be opened to the general public.

generalInfo.childRule: Performances are All Ages unless otherwise noted. Everyone must have a ticket to enter the venue. Parents are encouraged to use reasonable discretion as some concerts/events are not suitable for children.

venues.parkingDetail: From Route 93 (North or South): Medford Square is easily accessed from Route 93. Take Exit 32 for Rt. 60 West. At the rotary, follow the parking attendant who will direct you to the suggested parking behind Medford City Hall. From Route 2 (East or West): From Route 2 take Exit 59 and follow the signs for Route 60 East. Stay on Route 60 East through Arlington, and into Medford. Route 60 goes right into Medford Square. When you get to the main intersection in the middle of the square take Riverside Drive to City Hall Mall where you will find the suggested parking behind Medford City Hall. There is also plenty of on street paring (Free after 6pm) and municipal parking lots within a few blocks of the theatre.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible seating policy: The Chevalier Theatre places high priority on the comfort and safety of its patrons. The Chevalier Theatre also recognizes the needs of people with disabilities, as defined by the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) of 1990. Every effort has been made to comply with both ADA and Commonwealth accessibility guidelines to accommodate patrons with disabilities. Accessible seating can be purchased directly via www.ticketmaster.com. Accessible seats will be marked with an ADA icon. For assistance purchasing ADA seats online, please contact Ticketmaster customer service at 800-653-8000. PLEASE NOTE: When a show is over 85% sold any unsold accessible seating will be opened to the general public.

generalInfo.generalRule: Rules and Restrictions: All events take place rain or shine. No refunds or exchanges. No lawn chairs. No food or beverages (except factory-sealed bottles of water). There is NO SMOKING allowed anywhere at the venue. No Re-Admission Ticket limit of 8 per purchase is standard (with some exceptions). Backpacks and Large Bags: Rockland Trust Bank Pavilion strongly discourages customers from bringing backpacks and large bags (over 1 gallon size) to the Pavilion. All backpacks and large bags will be subject to a thorough inspection at a designated entry gate and may delay your entry into the Pavilion. Camera Policy: Personal, non-professional cameras are allowed in the venue unless they are prohibited by the artist. Flash photography, video and removable lens cameras are not permitted without venue approval. Group Sales: No group discounts. Functions may be booked through the venue administration office. Weapons Prohibited: Guests, including law enforcement personnel not present in an official capacity, are prohibited from bringing weapons into the venue. Rockland Trust Bank Pavilion does not provide weapon lockers. Weapons may not be checked in at the Guest Services kiosk. Weapons include, but are not limited to, the following: firearms, explosives, stun guns, handcuffs, brass knuckles, sticks, clubs, batons, martial arts instruments, pepper spray, tear gas, and knives with blades over 2 inches in length. Guests found in possession of the above-mentioned items will be asked to remove the item from the venue or dispose of it. Guests who refuse to comply will be evicted from the venue.
generalInfo.childRule: Children (babies in arms) under 2 years are free if seated in the lap of a ticketed adult. All other children are allowed with a full priced ticket.

generalInfo.generalRule: No bottles, cans, outside food or beverages (including alcohol), any item that can be used as a weapon. No dress code for concerts. ALL SALES ARE FINAL. NO REFUNDS OR EXCHANGES. Camera Policy: Personal cameras are allowed in the venue. Flash photography, video and removable lens cameras are not permitted without venue approval. Lighters are not allowed in the venue and there is absolutely NO SMOKING OR VAPING allowed at the venue per the city of Boston Ordinances. Any smoking or vaping will result in IMMEDIATE EJECTION from the event. All bags larger than 10 in x 9 in, backpacks, professional cameras (i.e detachable lenses), video equipment, luggage, and like articles are strictly prohibited. Please make sure necessary arrangements are made ahead of time as these items are not allowed on the premise. All patrons subject to search upon venue entry. Any medication must be accompanied with proof of prescription. Other prohibited items: drug paraphernalia, weapons, knives, liquid containers, selfie sticks, tablets, laptops, outside food or drinks, any gang affiliated apparel or accessories including bandanas, laser pointers, glass, any LED apparel, candy or beaded jewelry, masks, glow sticks, toys, furry boots, etc.

venues.parkingDetail: From Route 93 (North or South): Medford Square is easily accessed from Route 93. Take Exit 32 for Rt. 60 West. At the rotary, follow the parking attendant who will direct you to the suggested parking behind Medford City Hall. From Route 2 (East or West): From Route 2 take Exit 59 and follow the signs for Route 60 East. Stay on Route 60 East through Arlington, and into Medford. Route 60 goes right into Medford Square. When you get to the main intersection in the middle of the square take Riverside Drive to City Hall Mall where you will find the suggested parking behind Medford City Hall. There is also plenty of on street paring (Free after 6pm) and municipal parking lots within a few blocks of the theatre.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible seating policy: The Chevalier Theatre places high priority on the comfort and safety of its patrons. The Chevalier Theatre also recognizes the needs of people with disabilities, as defined by the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) of 1990. Every effort has been made to comply with both ADA and Commonwealth accessibility guidelines to accommodate patrons with disabilities. Accessible seating can be purchased directly via www.ticketmaster.com. Accessible seats will be marked with an ADA icon. For assistance purchasing ADA seats online, please contact Ticketmaster customer service at 800-653-8000. PLEASE NOTE: When a show is over 85% sold any unsold accessible seating will be opened to the general public.

generalInfo.generalRule: Cumberland County has announced new screening and hygiene protocols to prevent the spread of COVID-19 at events held at the Cross Insurance Arena. The new rules align the Arena with state and local recommendations, as well as guidance from the Federal CDC regarding protection against spreading COVID-19 in contained spaces. Effective October 22, attendees of events at the arena age 12 and over will need to provide evidence of vaccination against COVID-19, or a recent negative test taken within 72 hours of the event. Mask wearing is strongly recommended inside the Arena. Attendees who are too young to be vaccinated must wear a mask while attending events inside the Arena but do not need to provide a negative COVID-19 test. The new protocols will remain in place until further notice, but are likely to change based on the severity of the pandemic in Cumberland County and as vaccination becomes available for more age groups.

venues.parkingDetail: We provide ample parking for the events right on the property. A parking pass is required of every vehicle looking to enter the property for the events. There are several different kinds of parking passes including overnight tent site parking passes. Please see the different parking options below. Our parking areas typically open 3 to 4 hours before the show starts. Please review the times on our website as they can change and the time on your tickets and/or passes may no longer be accurate. $65 Ultimate Bath VIP Parking (East) $55 Ultimate Bath VIP Parking (West) $40 Kubota Prime Tailgate Parking $30 MB Tractor Premium Parking $15 Orange Standard Parking $75 Limo/RV Parking $65 Kittery Trading Post Overnight Tent Sites
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: ADA tickets can be purchased online via www.livenation.com. You do not need to call the box office to place an order as all of our accessible tickets are available through www.livenation.com. Look for the logo on the Find Tickets page to view all available accessible seats. We do have accessible seating in every price range, but be advised it does occasionally sell out. We have very limited seating available for guests on the day of the event so please make sure you purchase accessible seating when you order tickets.

generalInfo.generalRule: What is Allowed in the Gates? The following is a list of items and whether they are typically allowed into the venue or not. Sometimes a specific tour may require a different policy on certain items. All items that are allowed in are subject to a thorough search from our security team. »Bags or Purses? No, except for a small clutch purse or a clear tote with a maximum size of 12" Wide x 12" High x 6" Deep. »Lawn Chairs? Chair rentals are available for $5! Pick them up when you arrive and then leave them where they are when you leave. Fast, simple and hassle-free! (If you wish to bring your own lawn chair, please be aware that they MUST adhere to the size limitation policy and you will have a thorough search at a specific location that will make entry in the venue slower.) »Blankets? If you have a lawn seating ticket, yes. »Food & Drink? No, except for one factory-sealed bottle of water, 20 oz. or less, per person »Refillable Water Bottles? Yes, but only completely empty. There are fill stations inside. »Coolers? No. »Weapons? No. »Cameras? Yes but only non-professional without a detachable lens. »IPads? No. »Video Camera? No. »Selfie Sticks? No. »Drugs? No. »Medications? Yes, but only in the original prescription container with matching ID. »Pets? No. »Poster Tubes? Yes. »Umbrellas? Yes, but may not be open during the performance. We recommend quality rain gear. »Signs? Yes, but please be courteous to others. Lawn Seating The lawn seating is a general admission area behind the reserved pavilion seats. It is not covered and therefore, is exposed to the elements. In the event of inclement weather, we recommend quality rain gear. Umbrellas are allowed but may not be open during the performances. Smoking is prohibited except in one section to the far right of the lawn. If you have trouble walking up inclined surfaces, lawn seating may not be the best option for you. If lawn seating is your only option, please see our staff for assistance. Traffic Please plan ahead and allow for plenty of extra time in the event of heavy traffic so that you do not miss any of the earlier performances. We open the parking lots hours early to accommodate all those that want to arrive early. Drop-Offs & Pick-Ups Please arrive before the rush on both ends of a pick-up and drop-off and do so at the Main Entrance off of Route 11B in Gilford -- 72 Meadowbrook Ln. Tailgating We have several parking areas and we condone and even, promote, responsible tailgating. Tailgating can be a very big part of making the event fun and memorable for you. That being said, the possession or consumption of alcoholic beverages, in our parking areas, actually violates a local Gilford ordinance. Underage drinking and/or intoxication, will most certainly cause you to miss the show and may lead to being arrested. Weather All performances will go on rain or shine. In the event of a weather emergency, like a hurricane, events will most likely be rescheduled. In the event of inclement weather, please use quality rain gear. Umbrellas are allowed but may not be open during performances. Umbrellas Umbrellas are allowed inside the venue and we allow all types of chairs and blankets in the lawn area. We ask that you are courteous and keep your umbrella closed during the performance to not obstruct anyone's view. We recommend wearing ponchos or other rain gear. The show will go on rain or shine. Weapons There are absolutely no weapons of any kind permitted into the venue including small pocket knives. There will be bag searches and pat downs. Any weapons discovered on an individual attempting to enter the venue will be confiscated and we will not be able to return that item to you at any time. Pets There are no pets allowed anywhere on the property. Please contact the box office in advance to coordinate the use of any kind of service animal. No Re-entry Once you enter the pavilion, you will not be permitted to leave the venue and re-enter again so please be sure to bring everything you need with you the first time. Be sure to have your photo ID with you as everyone is carded for alcohol service. Doors The doors or gates to our midway typically open between 90 and 120 minutes prior to the main stage performances starting. We usually have a lot going on include excellent regional acts playing on the Magic Hat Stage so please come in early, enjoy everything we have to offer and assure your party not missing any of the show all at the same time. Resale Tickets When the artist approves to do so, we offer our customers the ability to buy and sell tickets directly from each other for their convenience, comfort and security. For more information on our resell program, go here. Ticket Information There are no refunds or exchanges on any tickets for any event. GROUP SALES Contact Aubrey at AubreyBrooks@LiveNation.com
